text.tspan: Lessons are offered Monday - Friday afternoons and all day on Sundays. Students will learn
horse grooming, riding and tack care. Our desire is to instill a passion for the animal into
others. We specialize in the younger equestrians!
Camps for girls are offered during summer and winter break. There is maximum of 6 riders
per session. Each child is given their own horse for a week. All aspects of horse ownership and
care are taught. The hours are 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Monday - Friday with before and after camp
care available. Lunch, snacks and lot of fluids are provided.
We have access over 6000 acres of Florida's natural habitat to enjoy. We regularly see deer,
turkey, alligators, wild boar and many species of birds. We adjust our rides to the riding ability
of the client. We offer hourly to whole day with lunch provided.
